AR02 - The Real Book

The Real Book is an 828-page publication conceived by first-year architecture students at EPFL under the guidance of the ALICE laboratory (Atelier de la Conception de l'Espace), born out of the COVID-19 confinement of spring 2020. It documents the work that would have taken shape along the banks of the Rhône and Arve rivers in Geneva — a collective project reimagined through drawings, collages and digital representations — and was later selected as one of the most beautiful Swiss books by the Federal Office of Culture. I contributed to this collective endeavour as a first-year student.
